In summary,we present the first search for the radia tive leptonic decay $D ^ { + } ~ 	o ~ \gamma e ^ { + } 
u _ { e }$ in the charm sector based on a DT method using a data sample of $2 . 9 3 \mathrm { f b } ^ { - 1 }$ collected with the BESIII detector at a center-of-mass energy $\sqrt { s } = 3 . 7 7 3 \mathrm { G e V }$ . No significant $D ^ { + } 	o \gamma e ^ { + } 
u _ { e }$ signal is observed.With a 10 MeV cutoff on the radiative photon energy,the upper limit of the decay branching fraction for $D ^ { + } 	o \gamma e ^ { + } 
u _ { e }$ is $B ( D ^ { + } 	o \gamma e ^ { + } 
u _ { e } ) < 3 . 0 	imes 1 0 ^ { - 5 }$ at the 90% C.L.The result approaches the theoretical predictions in Refs.[11, 12];more data may help to discriminate among the full suite of theoretical models.
